'''Sandro Salvini''' (1890–1955) was an Italian [[actor]]. He appeared in around thirty films during the [[silent film|silent]] and [[sound film|sound]] eras. He played the lead role of the Duke in [[Alessandro Blasetti]]'s ''[[Mother Earth (film)|Mother Earth]]'' (1931).<ref>Landy p.178-79</ref> His grandfather was the famous 19th century Italian stage tragedian [[Tommaso Salvini]].

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[The Thirteenth Man]]'' (1917)
* ''[[The Conqueror of the World]]'' (1919)
* ''[[Countess Sarah]]'' (1919)
* ''[[The Cheerful Soul]]'' (1919)
* ''[[The Fall of the Curtain]]'' (1920)
* ''[[The Serpent (1920 film)|The Serpent]]'' (1920)
* ''[[Little Sister (1921 film)|Little Sister]]'' (1921)
* ''[[The Stronger Passion]]'' (1921)
* ''[[Nero (1922 film)|Nero]]'' (1922)
* ''[[The Shepherd King]]'' (1923)
* ''[[Mother Earth (film)|Mother Earth]]'' (1931)
* ''[[Lorenzino de' Medici (film)|Lorenzino de' Medici]]'' (1935)
* ''[[Kean (1940 film)|Kean]]'' (1940)

